# Dispatcher control — operator-side remote control for the god-session

Operate the always-on god-session running on the VPS configured in this project's `.env.local`. The session lives entirely on the VPS; this slash-command is your local control plane.

## Configuration (read from `.env.local`, not hardcoded)

Before running any subcommand, source `.env.local` from the current repo:

```bash
[ -f .env.local ] && set -a && . .env.local && set +a
: "${VPS_HOST:?missing VPS_HOST in .env.local}"
: "${VPS_SSH_KEY:?missing VPS_SSH_KEY in .env.local}"
: "${VPS_BOT_USER:?missing VPS_BOT_USER in .env.local}"
: "${VPS_PROJECT_NAME:?missing VPS_PROJECT_NAME in .env.local}"
: "${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX:?missing VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX in .env.local}"
: "${VPS_PROJECT_DIR:?missing VPS_PROJECT_DIR in .env.local}"
: "${VPS_RELAY_HOOK_PORT:?missing VPS_RELAY_HOOK_PORT in .env.local}"
: "${VPS_DISPATCH_COMMAND_NAME:?missing VPS_DISPATCH_COMMAND_NAME in .env.local}"
: "${VPS_AGENT_SKILLS_DIR:?missing VPS_AGENT_SKILLS_DIR in .env.local}"
: "${VPS_AGENT_SKILLS_PLUGINS:?missing VPS_AGENT_SKILLS_PLUGINS in .env.local}"
: "${VPS_GIT_PROVIDER:?missing VPS_GIT_PROVIDER in .env.local (github|gitlab)}"
: "${VPS_REPO_SLUG:?missing VPS_REPO_SLUG in .env.local}"
```

Required keys in `.env.local` (this file is git-ignored, never commits real values):

| Key | Example | Used for |
|---|---|---|
| `VPS_HOST` | `203.0.113.42` | SSH target (IP or hostname) |
| `VPS_SSH_KEY` | `~/.ssh/myproj_vps` | Path to private key |
| `VPS_BOT_USER` | `agent-bot` | Linux user owning the workload (typically UID 1000) |
| `VPS_PROJECT_NAME` | `myproj-skills-lab` | State/config dir name: `/etc/<NAME>/`, `/var/lib/<NAME>/`, `/var/log/<NAME>-god.log` |
| `VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX` | `myproj` | Per-project systemd unit + binary + tmux prefix: `<PFX>-god.service`, `<PFX>-dispatch.timer`, `/usr/local/bin/<PFX>-god`. (`agent-update.timer` is system-wide, no prefix.) |
| `VPS_PROJECT_DIR` | `/opt/myproj` | Cloned repo root on VPS |
| `VPS_GIT_PROVIDER` | `github` or `gitlab` | Selects which CLI / API the dispatcher and `queue` subcommand use |
| `VPS_REPO_SLUG` | `me/myproj` (github) or `group/project` (gitlab) | Repo path on the chosen provider; used in `queue` and dispatch.md |
| `VPS_RELAY_HOOK_PORT` | `9999` | Localhost HTTP port for the project relay-bot |
| `VPS_DISPATCH_COMMAND_NAME` | `myproj-dispatch` | Slash command name injected by `${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-dispatch.timer` |
| `VPS_AGENT_SKILLS_DIR` | `/opt/myproj-agent-skills` | Local clone of `levnikolaevich/claude-code-skills` on the VPS |
| `VPS_AGENT_SKILLS_PLUGINS` | `agile-workflow` | Selected marketplace plugins (`agile-workflow`, `all`, or comma-list) |

> Keep `VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX` explicit. Set it equal to `VPS_PROJECT_NAME` unless the deployment intentionally separates state/config name from service/binary prefix.

## Source map (resolved from .env at runtime)

| Field | Resolved value |
|---|---|
| Server | `${VPS_HOST}` (UID 1000 = `${VPS_BOT_USER}`) |
| Repo | `${VPS_REPO_SLUG}` on `${VPS_GIT_PROVIDER}`, cloned at `${VPS_PROJECT_DIR}` |
| systemd unit (god) | `${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-god.service` (Restart=always, MemoryMax=2G) |
| systemd unit (scheduler) | `${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-dispatch.timer` + `.service` (hourly :07) |
| systemd unit (maintenance) | `agent-update.timer` + `.service` — **system-wide** (one updater per VPS, restarts all god-services) |
| Skills marketplace repo | `${VPS_AGENT_SKILLS_DIR}` (`${VPS_AGENT_SKILLS_PLUGINS}` selected) |
| tmux session | `${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-god` |
| God wrapper | `/usr/local/bin/${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-god` |
| Relay-bot | `${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-relay-bot.service` (HTTP API on 127.0.0.1:${VPS_RELAY_HOOK_PORT}, SQLite at `/var/lib/${VPS_PROJECT_NAME}/relay.db`) |
| Slash command | `/home/${VPS_BOT_USER}/.claude/commands/${VPS_DISPATCH_COMMAND_NAME}.md` |
| Log (wrapper) | `/var/log/${VPS_PROJECT_NAME}-god.log` |
| State dir | `/var/lib/${VPS_PROJECT_NAME}/` |
| Bootstrap skill | `claude-code-skills/skills-catalog/ln-030-vps-bootstrap/SKILL.md` |

All SSH calls use `mcp__hex-ssh__remote-ssh` with `host=${VPS_HOST}`, `user=root`, `privateKeyPath=${VPS_SSH_KEY}`.

## Subcommands

`$ARGUMENTS` selects which one. Default: `status`.

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `status` | Health: systemd units, timers, tmux session, claude proc, relay-bot, queue, GH App, RAM, recent dispatches |
| `run-now` | Inject `/${VPS_DISPATCH_COMMAND_NAME}` into the live tmux pane (immediate dispatch run, in addition to hourly timer) |
| `refresh-god` | Kill tmux session + restart god service. Fresh claude session (memories persist via SessionStart hook) |
| `attach` | Print SSH command for interactive tmux attach |
| `tail [N]` | Last N lines of wrapper log (default 50) |
| `queue` | List open issues from `${VPS_REPO_SLUG}` (uses `gh` for github, `glab` for gitlab) |
| `pause` | `systemctl stop` god — kill session |
| `resume` | `systemctl start` god — re-enable |
| `install` | Idempotent verify after server rebuild |
| `logs` | Tail tmux pane (~80 lines of live claude conversation) |
| `audit [N]` | Last N dispatch runs from relay-bot SQLite — issue, phases, verdicts, PR (default 10) |
| `memory` | List persistent memories injected into each new session |

