## run-now

```bash
mcp__hex-ssh__remote-ssh:
  "sudo -u ${VPS_BOT_USER} tmux send-keys -t ${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-god '/${VPS_DISPATCH_COMMAND_NAME}' Enter ; \
   sleep 3 ; \
   sudo -u ${VPS_BOT_USER} tmux capture-pane -t ${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-god -p -S -200 | tail -30"
```

Watch progress with `/dispatcher logs`. Inspect structured run record: `/dispatcher audit 1`.

## refresh-god

```bash
mcp__hex-ssh__remote-ssh:
  "sudo -u ${VPS_BOT_USER} tmux kill-session -t ${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-god 2>/dev/null ; \
   systemctl restart ${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-god.service ; \
   sleep 12 ; \
   systemctl is-active ${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-god.service ; \
   sudo -u ${VPS_BOT_USER} tmux ls 2>&1"
```

Claude takes ~30s to fully boot; SessionStart hook will inject memories+lineage from relay-bot SQLite.

## attach

```
ssh -i "${VPS_SSH_KEY}" -t ${VPS_BOT_USER}@${VPS_HOST} "tmux attach -t ${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-god"
```

Detach: `Ctrl-b d`. Session keeps running.

