## Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Diagnosis | Recovery |
|---|---|---|
| `/dispatcher status` says god service inactive | `pause` was run, never resumed; or fresh server. | `/dispatcher resume` (or `/dispatcher install` for fresh). |
| tmux session missing while service active | Restart race window 0-15s. | Wait 15s and retry. If persistent, `journalctl -u ${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-god.service -n 50`. |
| Telegram inbound not getting replies | Relay-bot down OR hooks misconfigured. | `curl http://127.0.0.1:${VPS_RELAY_HOOK_PORT}/health` (relay), check journal of ${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-relay-bot.service. Verify settings.json hooks block exists. |
| Dispatch runs not firing hourly | `${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-dispatch.timer` not enabled. | `systemctl list-timers --no-pager` to verify; `systemctl enable --now ${VPS_SERVICE_PREFIX}-dispatch.timer` if missing. |
| Nightly CLI/plugin updates not running | System-wide `agent-update.timer` not enabled or unit missing. | `systemctl list-timers agent-update.timer --no-pager`; re-run ln-030 Step 7d if missing. |
| Claude/Codex skills missing | Step 5c was skipped or `VPS_AGENT_SKILLS_DIR` points to the wrong clone. | Re-run ln-030 Step 5c; verify manifests under `${VPS_AGENT_SKILLS_DIR}` and selected plugin entries in `~/.codex/config.toml`. |
| Relay outbox accumulating queued | Telegram outage. | `/dispatcher status` shows queue depth. Outbox auto-retries with backoff. |

